,null,{}],\"- Nigerian Arts in the Cycle of Life Gallery\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"- Nigerian Government: Yesterday and Today\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-montserrat uppercase sm:first-line:w-[80%] font-bold sm:text-[1rem] text-primary\",\"children\":\"   Other services of the National Museum Lagos include: \"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"w-fit flex flex-col gap-4 font-old text-[0.75rem] sm:text-[16px]\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Conservation and Restoration Services:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"National Museum Lagos has a conservation labs where they preserve and restore artifacts and artworks.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Retail Services:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"NML offers a gift shop where visitors can purchase cultural items, souvenirs, books, and other merchandise related to the museum's exhibits and collections.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Educational Programs:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Museums often offer educational workshops, lectures, and classes for visitors of all ages. These programs cover history, art, science, and more, tailored to students, adults, and families.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Organized/Guided Tours:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"National Museum Lagos provides guided tours led by knowledgeable docents. These tours offer in-depth information about the exhibits and enhance the visitor experience. It is ooen to schools (primary, secondary, and higher institutions), religious groups, clubs, organizations, and associations.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Children’s Day Program:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Celebrated annually with cultural activities aimed at teaching the Nigerian identity, morals, beliefs, and values.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Independence Day Celebration:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Celebrates Nigeria’s independence with participants mimicking nationalist dress and receiving handmade Nigerian flags.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Digital Resources:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"NML provides online access to parts of their collections, virtual tours, educational materials, and digital exhibitions, allowing broader access to their resources.\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"h-[100%] font-old  text-[0.75rem] sm:text-[16px] sm:w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-6 font-light w-full  border-black p-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[\"$L12\",\"NML provides online access to parts of their collections, virtual tours, educational materials, and digital exhibitions, allowing broader access to their resources.\"]}],\"$L13\",\"$L14\",\"$L15\",\"$L16\"]}]]}]\na:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"w-[100%] h-[100%] font-montserrat flex justify-between bg-background border-primary border-x-[1px] flex-col sm:flex-row columns-2 overflow-hidden\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"h-[100%] font-old  text-[0.75rem] sm:text-[16px] sm:w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-6 font-light w-full  border-black p-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Public Events:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"MNL host a variety of public events, including lectures, panel discussions and cultural performances, which are often related to current exhibitions or broader cultural topics.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Children's Digest Magazine Publication:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"A cultural magazine for children and adults, focusing on Nigerian artifacts, cultural norms, and values, and highlighting the museum's role in cultural preservation.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Exportation of Art Works/Cultural Items:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Facilitates the export of art pieces by public and private individuals or organizations to other countries.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Research Facilities:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"National Museums Lagos maintains her libraries, archives, and research centers for easy access to academic and historical resources. These facilities support personal development, scholars, students, and the general public in their research endeavors.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"h-[100%] font-old  text-[0.75rem] sm:text-[16px] sm:w-1/2 flex flex-col gap-6 font-light w-full border-black p-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Temporary Exhibitions:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"In addition to permanent collections, museums regularly organize temporary or traveling exhibitions that showcase different themes, artists, or periods, often in collaboration with other institutions. National Museum Lagos often hosts exhibitions of private or public art collections, drawing attention to the museum.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Venue Rental for Events:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"NML often rents out their spaces for private events, such as weddings, corporate gatherings, and parties, providing a unique and culturally rich environment for special occasions.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Children's Play Park:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"A designated area for children to learn, play, and have fun.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"In sum, the National Museum Lagos is a place of cultural significance, showcasing the richness of Nigeria's cultural heritage and values.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}]}]]}]]}]\nb:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"border-primary border-t-[1px] w-[100%] h-fit p-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-[1rem] sm:text-[3rem] pb-4\",\"children\":\"MEET THE CURATOR\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"font-old pb-8 flex w-fit h-fit flex-col gap-2 object-contain object-center\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"alt\":\"the curator\",\"quality\":100,\"src\":\"/assets/curator.webp\",\"className\":\"object-contain\",\"width\":200,\"height\":300}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[\"Nkechi Olatubosun Adedeji.( Mrs)\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"Curator, National Museum Lagos.\"]}]]}]]}]\nc:[\"$\",\"$L17\",null,{\"children\":[\"$L18\",[\"$\",\"$L19\",null,{\"promise\":\"$@1a\"}]]}]\nd:[\"$\",\"div\",\"l\",{\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"w-[100vw] h-[100vh] flex flex-col justify-center items-center font-montserrat bg-background gap-10 p-20\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"w-full h-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-10\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"svg\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":\"true\",\"className\":\"w-10 h-10 text-primary  fill-blue-600 animate-spin\",\"viewBox\":\"0 0 100 101\",\"fill\":\"none\",\"xmlns\":\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"path\",null,{\"d\":\"M100 50.5908C100 78.2051 77.6142 100.591 50 100.591C22.3858 100.591 0 78.2051 0 50.5908C0 22.9766 22.3858 0.59082 50 0.59082C77.6142 0.59082 100 22.9766 100 50.5908ZM9.08144 50.5908C9.08144 73.1895 27.4013 91.5094 50 91.5094C72.5987 91.5094 90.9186 73.1895 90.9186 50.5908C90.9186 27.9921 72.5987 9.67226 50 9.67226C27.4013 9.67226 9.08144 27.9921 9.08144 50.5908Z\",\"fill\":\"currentColor\"}],[\"$\",\"path\",null,{\"d\":\"M93.9676 39.0409C96.393 38.4038 97.8624 35.9116 97.0079 33.5539C95.2932 28.8227 92.871 24.3692 89.8167 20.348C85.8452 15.1192 80.8826 10.7238 75.2124 7.41289C69.5422 4.10194 63.2754 1.94025 56.7698 1.05124C51.7666 0.367541 46.6976 0.446843 41.7345 1.27873C39.2613 1.69328 37.813 4.19778 38.4501 6.62326C39.0873 9.04874 41.5694 10.4717 44.0505 10.1071C47.8511 9.54855 51.7191 9.52689 55.5402 10.0491C60.8642 10.7766 65.9928 12.5457 70.6331 15.2552C75.2735 17.9648 79.3347 21.5619 82.5849 25.841C84.9175 28.9121 86.7997 32.2913 88.1811 35.8758C89.083 38.2158 91.5421 39.6781 93.9676 39.0409Z\",\"fill\":\"currentFill\"}]]}]}]}]}]\ne:[\"$\",\"$1\",\"h\",{\"children\":[null,[[\"$\",\"$L1b\",null,{\"children\":\"$L1c\"}],[\"$\",\"meta\",null,{\"name\":\"next-size-adjust\",\"content\":\"\"}]],[\"$\",\"$L1d\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"hidden\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"$1e\",null,{\"fallback\":null,\"children\":\"$L1f\"}]}]}]]}]\n12:[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Digital Resources:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Cultural/Religious Festivals:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"NML organizes and participates in cultural festivals that celebrate different traditions, heritage, or religious values, bringing together diverse audiences. Some of such events are:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Eid-Fitr Program: Celebrates the end of Ramadan with cultural activities that remind the populace of their heritage.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Christmas Program: Organized for children, featuring Christmas items, cultural activities, games, songs, and dances to celebrate the Yuletide season.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Cultural Day Program: Promotes Nigerian culture through various cultural activities, showcasing the unity in Nigeria's cultural diversity.\"]}]\n14:[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Special Children Program:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Invites children to the museum or takes the museum to them, teaching cultural practices, skills, and more, giving them a sense of societal belonging. s, beliefs, and values.\"]}]\n15:[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Prison (Correctional Service) Outreach:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"Designed to reach the underserved population,  provides empowerment and vocational training to prisoners and extends this program to correctional officers' wives.\"]}]\n16:[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-primary font-montserrat\",\"children\":[\"Art Classes and Workshops:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}]]}],\"National Museum Lagos carries out art classes and workshops where participants can learn various artistic techniques, such as painting, sculpture, photography, and more. Such classes and workshops includes:\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Training the Trainers Program- trains school art teachers on museum artifacts and skills acquisition.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Skills Acquisition (Empowerment) Program-Teaches the production of essential items like vim, liquid soap, air fresheners, designed slippers, tie & dye (batik), local balm, Vaseline, insecticides, Ankara notepads, etc.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・The 'See, Feel, & Touch' Program- Enhances cultural teachings for secondary school students by allowing them to interact with replicas of Nigerian artifacts.\",[\"$\",\"br\",null,{}],\"・Long Holiday (Arts) Program- Engages secondary students interested in arts with activities like drawing and painting. ndmade Nigerian flags.\"]}]\n20:I[52619,[\"2619\",\"static/chunks/2619-024c323f8ca0f6aa.js\",\"4906\",\"static/chunks/4906-e5106e746380f2ce.js\",\"1536\",\"static/chunks/1536-62ed6ea3c6037259.js\",\"4561\",\"static/chunks/app/(app)/about/page-4e868e746decfb88.js\"],\"\"]\n21:I[2742,[\"2619\",\"static/chunks/2619-024c323f8ca0f6aa.js\",\"4906\",\"static/chunks/4906-e5106e746380f2ce.js\",\"4944\",\"static/chunks/app/(app)/layout-439b6b0374114d28.js\"],\"default\"]\n4:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex relative items-center justify-center w-[100%]  h-fit py-4 border-b-[1px] border-primary px-8 z-20\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"w-fit h-fit \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L20\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"justify-self-start\",\"style\":{\"paddingLeft\":\"1rem\",\"bottom\":\"4px\"},\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"width\":35,\"height\":40,\"src\":\"https://lagosmuseumarchives.ng/api/media/file/NCMM%20Logo.webp\",\"alt\":\"logo\",\"className\":\"aspect-square\"}]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L21\",null,{\"className\":\"\",\"pages\":[{\"label\":\"Intelligence Reports\",\"link\":\"intelligence_reports\"},{\"label\":\"Manuscripts\",\"link\":\"manuscripts\"},{\"label\":\"Maps\",\"link\":\"maps\"},{\"label\":\"Government\",\"link\":\"government_reports\"},{\"label\":\"Alternative Heritage Archival materials\",\"link\":\"alternative_heritage_archival\"},{\"label\":\"Alternative Heritage Museum objects and artefacts\",\"link\":\"alternative_heritages_objects\"}],\"alternative_heritages\":{\"docs\":[{\"id\":11,\"nav\":[{\"id\":\"68236556fc7a521286e6f2b0\",\"label\":\"Ethnographic\",\"link\":\"alternative_heritages_objects/ethnographic_objects\"}]},{\"id\":3,\"nav\":[{\"id